    "transliteration": "BISMILLAHIR RAHMANIR RAHEEM A'N JAABIRIBNE A'BDUL LAAHIL ANSAARI A'N FAATEMATAZ ZAHRAAE A'LAIHAS SALAAMO BINTE RASOOLIL LAAHE SALLAL LAAHO A'LAYHE WA AALEHI WA SALLAMA QAALAT SAME'TO FAATEMATA ANNAHAA QAALAT DAKHALA A'LAIYYA ABI RASOOLUL LAAHE FEE BA'ZIL AYYAAME FA QAALA ASSALAMO A'LAIKE YAA FATEMATO FA QULTO A'LAIKAS SALAAMO QAALA INNEE AJEDO FEE BADANI ZO'FAN FA QULTO LAHU OE'EZOKA BIL LAAHE YAA ABATAAHO MENAZ ZO'FE FA QAALA YAA FATEMATO EETINI BILKESAAA-IL YAMAANI FA GHAT-TEENI BEHI FA ATAYTOHU BEHI WA SIRTO ANZORO ELAYHE WA EZAA WAJHOHU YATALA'LAO KA-ANNAHUL BADRO FEE LAYLATE TAMAAMEHI WA KAMAALEHI (SALAWAAT) FAMA KAANAT ILLAA SAA-A'TAWN WA EZA BE WALADEYAL HASANE QAD AQBALA WA QAALA ASSALAAMO ALAYKE YAA UMMAAHO FA QULTO WA ALAIKAS SALAAMO YA QURRATE A'YNI WA SAMARATA FOAADI FA QAALA YAA UMMAAHO INNEE ASHUMMO I'NDAKE RAAA-EHATAN TAYYEBATAN KA AN NAHAA RAAA-EHATO JADDI RASOOLIL LAAHE FAQULTO NA-A'M INNA JADDAKA TAHTAL KESAAE FA AQBALAL HASANO NAHWAL KESAAA-E WA QAALA ASSALAAMO A'LAYKA YA JADDAAHO YAA RASOOLAL LAAHE ATA'ZANO LEE A'N ADKHOLA MA-A'KA TAHTAL KESAAA-E FA QAALA: \"WA A'LAYKAS SALAAMO YA WALADI WA YAA SAAHEBA HAUZI QAD AZINTO LAKA FA DAKHALA MA-A'HU TAHTAL KESAAA-E (SALAWAAT) FAMAA KAANAT ILLAA SAA-A'TAWN WA EZAA BE WALADEYAL HUSAYNE QAD AQBALA WA QAALA : \"ASSALAAMO A'LAYKE YAA UMMAAHO\" FA QULTO: \"WA ALAYKAS SALAAMO YAA WALADI WA YAA QURRATA A'YNI WA SAMARATO FOAADI\" FA QAALA LEE \"YAA UMMAAHO INNI ASHUMMO I'NDAKA RAA-EHATAN TAYYEBATAN KA ANNAHAA RAAEHATO JADDI RASOOLIL LAAHE\" FA QULTO : NA-A'M INNA JADDAKA WA AKHAAKA TAHTAL KESAAA-E\" FADANAL HUSAYNO NAHWAL KESAAA-E WA QAALA \"ASSALAAMO A'LAYKA YAA JADDAAHO ASSALAAMO ALAYKA YAA MANIKHTAARAHUL LAAHO ATA'ZANO-LEE A'N ADKHOLA MA-A'KOMA TAHTAL KESAAE? FA QAALA: \"WA ALAYKAS SALAAMO YAA WALADI, WA YAA SHAAFEA UMMATI QAD AZINTO LAKA\" FA DAKHALA MA-A'HOMA TAHTAL KESAAE.\r\n\r\n(SALAWAAT) FA AQBALA I'NDA ZAALEKA ABUL HASANE A'LIYYUBNO ABI TAALEBIN WA QAALA : \"ASSALAAMO A'LAYKE YAA BINTE RASOOLIL LAAHE\" FA QULTO \"WA A'LAYKAS SALAAMO YAA ABAL HASANE WA YAA AMEERAL MOMENEEN\". FA QAALA \"YAA FAATEMATO, INNI ASHUMMO I'NDAKA RAAEHATAN TAYYEBATAN KA ANNAHAA RAAEHATO AKHEE WABNE AMMI RASOOLIL LAAHE\" FA QULTO \"NA-A'M HAAHOWA MA-A' WALADAYKA TAHTAL KESAAA-E\" FA AQBALA A'LIYYUN NAHWAL KESAAE, WA QAALA \"ASSALAAMO ALAYKA YAA RASOOLAL LAAHE, ATA'ZANO LEE A'N AKOONA MA-A'KUM TAHTAL KESAAA-E? FA QAALA \"WA ALAYKASSALAAMO YAA AKHEE, WA YAA WASIYYEE WA KHALIFATEE WA SAAHEBA LEWAAA--EE QAD AZINTO LAKA\" FA DAKHALA A'LIYYUN TAHTAL KESAAA-E. (SALAWAAT) SUMMA ATAYTO NAHWAL KESAAA-E WA QULTO \"ASSALAAMO A'LAYKA YAA ABATAAHO, YAA RASOOLAL LAAHE ATA' ZANO LEE A'N AKOONA MA-A'KUM TAHTAL KESAAA-E? WA QAALA \"WA A'LAYKIS SALAAMO YAA BINTEE WA YAA BAZ-A'TEE QAD AZINTO LAKE\" FA DAKHALTO TAHTAL KESAAA-E. (SALAWAAT) FA LAMMAK TAMALNAA JAMEE-A'N TAHTAL KESAAA-E AKHAZA ABI RASOOLIL LAAHE BE TARAFAYIL KESAAA-E, WA AUMA-A BE YADEHIL YUMNA ELAS SAMAAE WA QAALA: ALLAAHUMMA INNA HAAAOOLAAE AHLO BAYTI, WA KHAASSATEE, WA HAAMMATEE LAHMOHUM LAHMI, WA DAMOHUM DAMI YO'LEMONI MAA YO'LEMOHUM WA YAHZONONI MAA YAHZONOHUM, ANAA HARBUN LEMAN HAARABAHUM WA SILMUN LEMAN SAALAMAHUM, WA ADUWWUN LEMAN A'ADAAHUM WA MOHIBBUN LEMAN AHABBAHUM INNAHUM MINNI WA ANA MINHUM FAJ-A'L SALAWAATAKA WA BARAKAATAKA WA RAHMATAKA WA GHUFRAANAKA WA RIZWANAKA A'LAYYA WA A'LAYHIM WA AZHIB ANHOMUR RIZSA WA TAHHIRHUM TATHEERAA. FA QAALALLAAHO AZZA WA JALLA YAA MALAAA-EKATEE WA YAA SUKKAANA SAMAAWAATEE INNEE MAA KHALAQTO SAMAAA-A'M MABNIYYATAN WA LAA ARZAN MADHIYYATAN WALAA QAMARAM MONIRAN WA LAA SHAMSAN MOZEE-A'TAN, WALAA FALAKAN YADOORO WALAA BAHRAYN YAJRI WALAA FULKAN YASRI, ILLAA FEE MAHABBATE HAA-OOLAAA-IL KHAMSATIL LAZEENA HUM TAHTAL KESAAA-E. FA QAALAL AMEENO JIBRAEELO YAA RABBE WA MAN TAHTAL KESAAA-E? FA QAALA AZZAWA JALLA HUM AHLO BAYTIN NOBUWWATE WA MA'DENUR RESAALATE HUM FAATEMATO WA ABOOHA WA BA'LOHAA WA BANOOHAA. (SALAWAAT) FA QAALA JABRAAA-EELO YAA RABBE ATA'ZANO LEE A'N AHBETA ELAL ARZE LE AKOONA MA-A'HUM SAADESAA. FA QAALALLAAHO NA-A'M QAD AZINTO LAKA. FAHABATAL AMEENO JABRAAA-EELO WA QAALAS SALAAMO A'LAYKA YAA RASOOLALLAAHE AL-A'LIYYUL A'ALAA YUQRE-OKAS SALAAMO WA YAKHUS-SOKA BITTAHIYYATE WAL IKRAAME WA YAQOOLO LAKA WA I'ZZATI WA JALAALI INNEE MAA KHALAQTO SAMAA-AN MABNIYYATAN WALAA ARZAN MADHIYYATAN WALAA QAMARAN MONEERAN WA LAA SHAMSAM MOZEE-ATAWN WA LAA FALAKAN YADOORO WALAA BAHRAN YAJRI WALAA FULKAN YASRI ILLAA LE AJLEKUM WA MAHABBATEKUM WA QAD AZENA LEE A'N ADKHOLA MA-A'KUM FA-HAL TA'ZANO LEE YAA RASOOLAL LAAHE. FA QAALA RASOOLAL LAAHE WA ALAYKAS SALAAMO YAA AMEENA WAHYIL LAAHE INNAHU NA-A'M QAD AZINTO LAKA FA DAKHALA JABRAAA-EELO MA-A'NA TAHTAL KESAAA-E. (SALAWAAT) FA QAALA LE ABI INNAL LAAHA QAD AWHAA ELAYKUM YAQOOLO INNAMAA YOREEDUL LAAHO LE YUZHEBA A'NKOMUR RIJSA AHLAL BAYTE WA YOTAHHERAKUM TATHEERAA. FA QAALA A'LIYYUN LE ABI YAA RASOOLAL LAAHE AKHBIRNI MAA LEJOLOOSENA HAAZA TAHTAL KESAAA-E MENAL FAZLE I'NDAL LAAHE. FA QAALAN NABIYYO WAL-LAZI BA-A'SANI BIL HAQQE NABBIYYAWN WASTAFAANI BIR RESAALATE NAJIYYAM MAA ZOKERA KHABARONA HAAZA FEE MAHFELIM MIN MAHAAFELE AHLIL ARZE, WA FEEHE JAM-U'M MIN SHEEA'TENAA WA MOHIBBEENA ILLAA WA NAZALAT A'LAYHEMUR RAHMATO WA HAFFAT BEHEMUL MALAAA-EKATO WAS-TAGHFARAT LAHUM ELAA AYN YATAFARRAQOO. FA QAALA A'LIYYUN A'LAYHIS SALAAMO EZAN WALLAAHE FUZNAA WA FAAZA SHEEA'TONA WA RABBIL KAA'BATE FA QAALAN NABIYYO SAANEYAN YAA A'LIYYO WALLAZI BA-A'SANI BIL HAQQE NABIYYAN WASTAFAANI BIR-RESAALATE NAJIYYAM MAA ZOKERA KHABARONA HAAZA FEE MAHAAFELIM MIN MAHAAFELE AHLIL ARZE WA FEEHE JAM-U'M MIN SHEEA'TENA WA MOHIBBEENA WA FEEHIM MAHMOOMUN ILLAA WA FAR-RAJAL LAAHO HAMMAHU WALAA MAGHMOOMUN ILLAA WA KASHAFAL LAAHO GHAMMAHU WALAA TAALEBO HAAJATIN ILLAA WA QAZAL LAAHO HAAJATAHU. FA QAALA A'LIYYUN A'LAYHIS SALAAMO EZAN WALLAAHE FUZNA WA SOI'DNAA WA KAZAALEKA SHEEA'TONAA FAAZU WA SOE'DOO FID DUNYAA WAL AAKHERAH WA RABBIL KA'BATE.", 
    "english": "Hadeeth-e-Kisa is that gracious description, which is a Tradition too and a description and an event too, a description of excellences also and a reason of prosperity too - Who is among the believers not aware of the words or meaning of this gracious Hadeeth, this is the Hadeeth healing the ill, the medium of fulfilling the desires of the desirous, supporting the helpless person engulfed in calamities - Just as this fact has also been mentioned itself in it that, by reciting it the mercy of Allah descends, and angels come and are busy asking for forgiveness - If recited before an owner of insight then better and spacious conditions are attained, if recited before a needy person then his needs are fulfilled, and since hundreds of years the believers are deriving the benefits of it's graces, and why should it not be? It is a recital of the owners of infallibility and purity, a mention of Siddiqa-e-Tahera (s.a.w.a), a commentary of the Holy Qur'an, an event of the assembly of Allah's lights, amazement and hope for the dwellers of Allah's throne and the greatness and excellence for the best of humans and it's pure roots - If, in presence of these specialities if grace, prosperity and mercy does not descend then when?\r\n\r\nOne day, my father the Messenger of Allah, peace be upon him and his Household, visited me, \"Peace be upon you, O Fatimah!\" he said.\r\n\r\nPeace be upon you, too. I answered.\r\n\r\nI can feel some fatigue in my body, he said to me, and I answered, \"I pray Allah to protect you O father against fatigue.\"\r\n\r\nFatimah, he ordered, \"bring me the Yemeni cloak and cover me with it.\"\r\n\r\nI brought him the Yemeni cloak and covered him with it. I then kept on looking at his face, which was glittering like a moon at the night of its fullness and perfection.\r\n\r\nNo more than a while passed when my son al-Hasan came in, \"Peace be upon you, mother!\" he greeted.\r\n\r\nPeace be upon you, too, O delight of my eye and fruit of my heart! I replied.\r\n\r\nO mother, he said, \"I can smell a pleasing scent as if it is the scent of my grandfather the Messenger of Allah, peace be upon him and his Household.\"\r\n\r\nYes, it is, I answered, \"Your grandfather is now under the cloak.\"\r\n\r\nAl-Hasan moved towards the cloak and said, \"Peace be upon you, O grandfather, Allah's Messenger. Will you allow me to be with you under this cloak?\"\r\n\r\nMy father replied, \"Peace be upon you too, my son and director of my Pond. I allow you.\"Al-Hasan then went under the cloak with his grandfather.\r\n\r\nNo more than another while passed before my son al-Husayn came in, \"Peace be upon you, mother!\" he greeted.\r\n\r\nPeace be upon you too, O my son, delight of my eye, and fruit of my heart, I replied.\r\n\r\nO Mother, he said, \"I can smell a pleasing scent as if it is the scent of my grandfather the Messenger of Allah.\"\r\n\r\nYes, I answered, \"Your grandfather and your bother are under the cloak.\"\r\n\r\nAl-Husayn then approached towards the cloak and said, \"Peace be upon you, O grandfather! Peace be upon you, O he whom Allah has chosen! Will you allow me to be with both of you under the cloak?\"\r\n\r\nMy father replied, \"Peace be upon you too, O my son and intercessor of my people. I allow you.\"\r\n\r\nAl-Husayn then went with them under the cloak.\r\n\r\nAt the same time, Abu'l-Hasan 'Ali ibn AbuTalib came in, \"Peace be upon you, daughter of Allah's Messenger,\" he greeted.\r\n\r\nPeace be upon you too, O Abu'l-Hasan and Commander of the Faithful, I replied.\r\n\r\nHe then said, \"Fatimah, I can smell a pleasing scent, as if it is the scent of my brother and cousin the Messenger of Allah.\"\r\n\r\nYes, I answered, \"He is there with your two sons under the cloak.\"\r\n\r\nAli moved towards the cloak and said, \"Peace be upon you, O Allah's Messenger! Will you allow me to be with you under the cloak?\"\r\n\r\nMy father replied, \"Peace be upon you too, O brother, successor, vicegerent, and bearer of my Pennon. I allow you.\"'Ali thus went with them under the cloak.\r\n\r\nI then came towards the cloak and said, \"Peace be upon you father, O Allah's Messenger. Will you allow me to be with you under the cloak?\"\r\n\r\nMy father replied, \"Peace be upon you too, my daughter and part of my flesh. I allow you.\" I thus went with them under the cloak.\r\n\r\nWhen all of us sat under the cloak, my father the Messenger of Allah took hold of the two edges of the cloak with one hand, pointed to the sky with his right hand, and prayed, \"O Allah! These are my true household, my unique people, and my kin. Their flesh is my flesh, their blood is my blood, whatever causes them pain causes me pain too, and whatever saddens them saddens me too. I am at war against whoever wages war against them, at peace with whoever is at peace with them, the enemy of whoever shows enmity towards them, and I love whoever loves them. They are part of me and I am part of them.\r\n\r\nTherefore (please) shower on me and them Your blessings, benedictions, mercy, forgiveness, and pleasure; remove from them filth and purify them with thorough purifying.\"\r\n\r\nMeanwhile, Allah the Almighty and All-majestic said, \"O My angels and inhabitants of My heavens! Verily, I have not created any well-established sky, extended land, glowing moon, shining sun, revolving planet, flowing ocean, or moving on ark except for the love of these five (individuals) who are now under the cloak.\"\r\n\r\nGabriel the Honest Archangel asked, \"O my Lord! Who are those under the cloak?\"\r\n\r\nThe Almighty and All-majestic Lord answered, \"They are the household of Prophethood and the core of the Message. They are namely F¡§imah, her father, her husband, and her sons.\"\r\n\r\nO my Lord, Gabriel asked, \"Will You allow me to descend to the earth to be the sixth of them?\"\r\n\r\nAllah the Almighty and All-majestic said, \"Yes, I allow you.\"\r\n\r\nGabriel the Honest Archangel descended, \"Peace be upon you, O Allah's Messenger!\" he greeted, \"The Most High and All-high (Lord) conveys to you His greeting, expresses His special greeting and honoring to you, and says, 'By My Almightiness and My Majesty I take this oath: I have not created any well-established sky, extended land, glowing moon, shining sun, revolving planet, flowing ocean, or moving on ark except for your sake and for your love.' He has then allowed me to join you (under this cloak). Will you, O Allah's Messenger, allow me?\"\r\n\r\nAllah's Messenger said, \"Peace be upon you, O trustee of Allah's Revelations. Yes, I allow you.\"\r\n\r\nSo, Gabriel joined us under the cloak. He thus said to my father, \"Allah has revealed to you saying, 'Allah only desires to keep away the uncleanness from you, O people of the House, and to purify you a thorough purifying.'\"\r\n\r\nAli then said to my father, \"O Allah's Messenger! Please tell me; what is the value of this gathering of us under this cloak in the sight of Allah?\"\r\n\r\nThe Prophet, peace be upon him and his Household, said, \"I swear this by Him Who has sent me with the truth as Prophet and chosen me, as holding communion, to convey the Message; whenever the tale of this gathering of us is mentioned in an assembly of the people of the earth in which a group of our adherents and lover are present, the (divine) mercy shall certainly be poured down on them and the angels shall certainly surround them, asking forgiveness for them until they depart.\"\r\n\r\nAli, peace be upon him, commented, \"Then, by Allah I swear it; we have won. So have our adherents. I swear it by the Lord of the Ka'bah.\"\r\n\r\nO 'Ali! my father Allah's Messenger, peace be upon him and his Household, added, \"I swear this by Him Who has sent me with the truth as Prophet and chosen me, as holding communion, to convey the Message; whenever the tale of this gathering of us is mentioned in an assembly of the people of the earth in which a group of our adherents and lover are present and among them there is a distressed one, Almighty Allah shall certainly release him from distress, or there is among them an aggrieved one, Almighty Allah shall certainly relieve him from grief, or there is among them one who needs a request to be granted, Almighty Allah shall certainly grant him his request.\"\r\n\r\nAli, peace be upon him, said, \"Then, we have won and attained pleasure. I swear it by Allah. So have our adherents; they have won and attained pleasure in this world and in the Hereafter. I swear it by the Lord of the Ka'bah.\""
